&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Nearform&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nearform is an independent team of data &amp;amp; AI experts, engineers, and designers who build intelligent digital solutions and capability at pace. We create AI-enabled solutions that enhance digital experiences, empower developers, and deliver measurable results. In these ways, we partner with ambitious enterprises to deliver enduring impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our deep expertise in solving the world’s most complex digital problems, along with our collaborative, people-first approach, enables enterprises to build breakthrough products and modernise legacy systems by unleashing the power of AI.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Today, our team of 500 experts in 20+ countries is trusted by leading enterprises including Lululemon, Puma, Sun Life, Starbucks, Travelex, Virgin Media 02, and Walmart.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced and commercially minded&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Senior People Business Partner or Head of People &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to join our People &amp;amp; Talent Team. Reporting to the Chief People Officer, you will partner with managers and senior leaders across the business to drive people strategy, organisational effectiveness, and high-performance cultures that support Nearform&#39;s continued growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a trusted advisor, you will work closely with managers and leaders to navigate complex people challenges, enable organisational change, and ensure that people decisions align with both business objectives and our values. You will play a key role in delivering an exceptional employee experience while helping to shape scalable people advisory practices across a globally distributed workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for a strategic HR professional who enjoys balancing operational excellence with long-term people planning and thrives in a fast-paced, high-growth environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Business Partnering&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with senior leaders and functional teams to align people strategies with business goals and commercial priorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide trusted advice and coaching on organisational design, workforce planning, performance, engagement, and talent management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build strong relationships with stakeholders across multiple regions and teams, influencing decision-making through insight and expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support managers and leaders in creating high-performing, inclusive, and engaged teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employee Relations &amp;amp; People Advisory&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and manage complex employee relations matters, providing pragmatic, risk-balanced advice to managers and stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach managers and leaders through performance management, capability concerns, organisational change, and sensitive people issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure consistent application of company policies, employment legislation, and people practices across relevant jurisdictions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with legal and external advisors where required on complex employment matters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
